<TITLE> Fire at Savar factory guts goods </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, Nov 14 (bdnews24.com)  A fire broke out Friday night at a readymade garment factory in Jamgara area in Savar, but no injury was reported, police said. The factory had called it a day only 15 minutes earlier, officials and witnesses said. Ashulia police said the fire at Green Life Fashions Limited broke out from the second floor of four-storey building at around 9:45pm. The blaze soon engulfed the whole factory, with flammable fabrics feeding the flames. Four units of local fire brigade rushed to the spot and brought the fire under control. The owner of the factory, Simon, who gave only one name, claimed he lost goods worth Tk 5 crore to the fire. Witnesses said cigarette caused the fire but fire brigade believed electrical short-circuit could be the reason. bdnews2
